what you're going through
right now is just a moment.

1387
01:27:01,266 --> 01:27:03,568
- A moment? A moment?
- Okay? And I-I feel exactly

1388
01:27:03,570 --> 01:27:05,370
what you're going through.
I think that you and I

1389
01:27:05,372 --> 01:27:07,205
should just get everybody gone,
we just talk.

1390
01:27:07,207 --> 01:27:08,773
I don't want to talk.
I want to go.

1391
01:27:08,775 --> 01:27:11,377
Well, Jared,
I don't want you to.

1392
01:27:11,379 --> 01:27:12,877
I want you to stay.

1393
01:27:12,879 --> 01:27:15,047
Well, I-I read the rules,

1394
01:27:15,049 --> 01:27:17,549
and none of them say
you can stop me from leaving.

1395
01:27:17,551 --> 01:27:19,418
I wouldn't... Can you just check
where Brandon is, please?

1396
01:27:19,420 --> 01:27:23,890
And if you or anyone puts their
hands on me, I have witnesses.

1397
01:27:23,892 --> 01:27:25,826
Nobody's gonna put
their hands on you.

1398
01:27:25,828 --> 01:27:28,895
Why-why would anybody do that?
Come and sit.

1399
01:27:28,897 --> 01:27:31,399
We're gonna wait
for your mom, okay?

1400
01:27:31,401 --> 01:27:34,168
VICTOR: Jesus, our savior,
please focus on Jared.

1401
01:27:34,170 --> 01:27:36,972
Let him see the strength
and courage that he needs.

1402
01:27:36,974 --> 01:27:38,974
I want you to fill him
right now with

1403
01:27:38,976 --> 01:27:40,308
all the wisdom
of everybody in this room

1404
01:27:40,310 --> 01:27:42,110
to show him
how much they love him

1405
01:27:42,112 --> 01:27:43,746
and how much
they care about him...

1406
01:27:43,748 --> 01:27:45,748
- Be strong!
- ...and his journey into

1407
01:27:45,750 --> 01:27:47,350
the fire that
he's walking into

1408
01:27:47,352 --> 01:27:49,653
- and what he's willing to face.
- You are a man.

1409
01:27:49,655 --> 01:27:52,021
Let him open his eyes to see
the wisdom that you have...

1410
01:27:52,023 --> 01:27:53,424
- NANCY (IN DISTANCE): Jared!
- Mom!

1411
01:27:53,426 --> 01:27:54,825
NANCY: Jared, honey,
what's happening?

1412
01:27:54,827 --> 01:27:56,093
- Mom! - What?
- Hey, hey! Sit back down!

1413
01:27:56,095 --> 01:27:57,261
Mom, they're not letting me go!

1414
01:27:57,263 --> 01:27:59,497
It's not that
we're not letting him go.

1415
01:27:59,499 --> 01:28:01,933
- Come on. Open this door.
- Just hold on, okay?

1416
01:28:01,935 --> 01:28:04,169
- Who are you?
- Mrs. Eamons, my name is Victor Sykes.

1417
01:28:04,171 --> 01:28:05,871
We spoke on the telephone.

1418
01:28:05,873 --> 01:28:07,172
I don't remember that.
Open the door.

1419
01:28:07,174 --> 01:28:08,874
- Well, I spoke with your husband a couple times.
- No.

1420
01:28:08,876 --> 01:28:10,108
Jared's just having
a moment here,

1421
01:28:10,110 --> 01:28:11,310
born out of
a role-playing exercise.

1422
01:28:11,312 --> 01:28:12,945
- Now be still. - It's fine.
- JARED: No, no!

1423
01:28:12,947 --> 01:28:14,714
That's not true.
Mom, tell him to open the door.

1424
01:28:14,716 --> 01:28:16,349
- BRANDON: You settle down.
- NANCY: No. Enough. - (POUNDING)

1425
01:28:16,351 --> 01:28:18,485
- Open the door now, Mr. Sykes.
- BRANDON: Shut up, okay?

1426
01:28:18,487 --> 01:28:21,455
- Listen, can we just all...
- I said open the door now!

1427
01:28:21,457 --> 01:28:23,491
